description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, motivated and conscientious individual to join our Palliative Care Team. We are looking for a highly motivated and enthusiastic nurse with advanced evidence based Palliative Care Skills with evidence of Palliative Care courses / Skills along with a V300 prescribing qualification and proven advanced communication skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our vision is to provide a comprehensive and patient-centred approach to admission avoidance, creating a forward thinking and innovative approach to managing people with multiple pathology and complex health needs. The focus of the role is to provide clinical expertise and leadership and to be accountable for the effective management of staff and resources. The role requires an understanding of current Initiatives in end of life care. The successful candidate will work as part of a team consisting of General Practitioners and Advanced Nurse Practitioners working within a new community service. You will liaise with other professionals from primary care and the acute trust to negotiate the admission of patients into our service. This post will suit someone with the right approach and a flexible “can do” attitude. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have an excellent staff supervision system enabling our staff to be committed to developing both their service and themselves through continued professional development and appraisal systems.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Shortlisting is planned for 18th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews are planned for 25th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
